@startuml ViewSessionCalendarSequenceDiagram

actor "User" as user
participant "Client" as client
participant "Controller" as controller
participant "Service" as service
database "Database" as db

== View Course Calendar ==

user -> client: 1. Navigate to course details
client -> controller: 2. GET /courses/:id
activate controller

controller -> service: 3. findOne(id)
activate service

service -> db: 4. Query course with sessions
activate db
db --> service: Course with sessions[]
deactivate db

service --> controller: Response with sessions
deactivate service

controller --> client: 5. HTTP 200
deactivate controller

client --> user: 6. Display course calendar view
note right of client
  Calendar grid showing all sessions
  with their dates and times
end note

== Filter Sessions by Date ==

user -> client: 7. Select date range or month
client --> client: 8. Filter/group sessions locally
note right of client
  Group sessions by week or month
  Apply date range filter
end note

client --> user: 9. Update calendar display
note right of user
  Calendar updates to show
  filtered sessions
end note

== View Session Details ==

user -> client: 10. Click on session in calendar
client --> user: 11. Show session details popup
note right of client
  Display:
  - Session date & time
  - Duration
  - Location/Court
  - Enrolled participants count
  - Status
end note

== View Availability ==

user -> client: 12. Check session availability
client --> user: 13. Show availability info
note right of client
  Display available/full status
  Show spaces remaining
  Display enrollment button if available
end note

@enduml
